\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "lem:endpoint-dominating-lemma"

\end_inset

The measure 
\begin_inset Formula $r\left(\cdot,1\mid z,t\right)\times r^{*}\left(\cdot,0\mid z,t\right)$
\end_inset

 is dominated by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}_{0,1}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}_{t}-a.e.$
\end_inset

 Accordingly, the density of 
\begin_inset Formula $r\left(\cdot,1\mid z,t\right)\times r^{*}\left(\cdot,0\mid z,t\right)$
\end_inset

 with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}_{0,1}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{r\left(dy,1\mid z,t\right)\times r^{*}\left(dx,0\mid z,t\right)}{\mathbb{R}_{0,1}\left(dx\times dy\right)}=\frac{r\left(y,1\mid z,t\right)r^{*}\left(x,0\mid z,t\right)}{c\left(x,y\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

